name: Wardown Park Orchard
short_description: Heritage fruit trees by the lake.
description: Publicly accessible apple and pear trees located near the museum and lakeside path.

name: Bury Park Incredible Edible
short_description: Urban herb planters in the town center.
description: Street-side planters with hardy herbs like rosemary and thyme for public use.

name: Bramingham Wood Wild Garlic
description: A prime spot for wild garlic (ramsons) throughout the woodland floor in spring.

name: Stockwood Park Hazelnuts
short_description: Hazel trees in parkland and woods.
description: Mature hazel trees can be found along the wooded perimeter of the golf course and park.

name: River Lea Path Berries
description: Inland riparian foraging along the Upper Lea path, offering abundant blackberries.

name: Bradgers Hill Sloes
short_description: Blackthorn bushes on the chalk downland.
description: A chalk grassland site perfect for finding sloes in the autumn.

name: Wigmore Park Fruit Trees
short_description: Scattered fruit trees in open parkland.
description: Urban park area with several public-access apple and damson trees.

name: Galley Hill Rosehips
short_description: Wild roses on the Chiltern edge.
description: Great rural foraging for rosehips and hawthorn berries along the hill crest.

name: Luton Town Centre Herbs
short_description: Central herb planters near St Mary's.
description: Small community planters with chives, parsley, and edible flowers.

name: Putteridge Walnuts
short_description: Public walnut trees in rural fringe.
description: Scattered walnut trees found along the boundary of the Putteridge Bury estate.

name: Popes Meadow Elder
short_description: Elder shrubs in the urban park.
description: Heavy cropping elder bushes found in the shrubberies around the edge of the meadow.

name: Cowridge Common Sweet Chestnuts
description: Occasional sweet chestnut trees available in the wooded sections of the common.

name: Luton Hoo Estuary Path 'Sea' Greens
description: As Luton is landlocked, find wild celery and meadowsweet along the damp edges of the Hoo estate paths.

name: Stopsley Common Sloes
description: Mature hedgerows around the sports fields offer heavy crops of sloes and hips.

name: Dallow Downs Hawthorn
description: Search the ancient hedgerows for haws and late-season blackberries.
